  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_91_11",
    "text": "Based on the schemas defined in problem 1, the following embedded SQL program accepts the id of an employee as input, and output all skills of the employee. Please fill in the blanks of the program.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14989732965229027,
      0.4738372089656217,
      0.831622168335763,
      0.5203488368044793
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_91",
    "order": 13
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_91_12",
    "text": "main() EXEC SQL INCLUDE SQLCA; EXEC SQL BEGIN DECLARE SECTION; char id[10]; char skill [20]; EXEC SQL END DECLARE SECTION; EXEC SQL CONNECT TO skill_db USER usel USING password 1; EXEC SQL DECLARE skill_cursor CURSOR for D printf(\"please input employee id :\"); scanf (\"%s\", id); EXEC SQL 2 for (;) EXEC SQL 3 if C _ break; printf( \"%sl n\", id);",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
